                         The underlying intuition is that the attention mechanism should reveal strongly correlated token pairs. As the proposed context-indexed vocabulary extension expects a clear structure of event context, applicable collectives, and connotation. One could envision a pipeline for extracting such extensions from corpora of literary and art-historical criticism. Furthermore, given that large language models are likely to have learned the historical context of tropes during their pre-training, it may be feasible to recover this embedded knowledge through carefully designed prompting.
